Indexes

The summary and supplemental indexes are a combination of environmental and residential population information. For each of the environmental indicators, there is a Summary Index and a Supplemental Summary Index. The indexes for a selected area are compared to those for all other locations in the state or nation.

SUMMARY INDEXES

The summary indexes help users screen for potential concerns. To do this, the summary index combines data on low income and POC populations with a single environmental indicator.
